<asp:Content id="Content1" runat="server" contentplaceholderid="ContentPlaceHolder1">
    <br />
    <table border="0" cellPadding="0" cellSpacing="0" width="60%" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td height="46" align="center">
		<div align="center">
			<b style="font-family: Cambria">PRODUCT INFORMATION</b></div>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<table border="0" cellPadding="0" cellSpacing="0" height="77" width="80%" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td height="81">
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">Directional Insight International, Inc. takes a business-oriented approach to the selection and development of employees.&nbsp; We assist organizations in making more informed hiring decisions and developing employees to their maximum potential by offering extensively validated assessment tools.</p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">The <strong>NSight&copy</strong> is an extensively validated, business-oriented human resources assessment instrument that measures a person's work-related characteristics and helps identify the right people for specific jobs.&nbsp; By matching people with jobs, the <strong>NSight&copy</strong> helps people make the right career choices so that they may find success and satisfaction in their workplace.&nbsp; Through the use of the <strong>NSight&copy</strong>, individuals can avoid working at jobs where they may be potentially uncomfortable, unhappy and prone to failure.</p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">Our most popular <span class="auto-style9">NSight&copy</span><span class="auto-style8"> package is the</span><span class="auto-style9"> NSight&copy Aptitude and Personality Questionnaire (NAPQ)</span><span class="auto-style8">.&nbsp; The </span><span class="auto-style9">NAPQ </span><span class="auto-style8">measures three aspects of aptitude (verbal reasoning/comprehension, numerical reasoning and word knowledge), one dimension of achievement (visual perception) and nineteen personality characteristics.&nbsp; The personality characteristics break down into the following six sub-topics: Decision Making/Problem Solving Skills, Drives, Stress, Interpersonal Communications, Leadership, Commitment/Persistence.  The investment per individual assessment that entails an 11-page analysis supported by a comprehensive telephone consultation detailing the results of NAPQ in relationship to the position under review is $210.&nbsp; However, quantity pricing that enhances affordability can be viewed by clicking </span> <a href="javascript:myopen()"><span class="auto-style8">here</span></a><span class="auto-style8">.</span></p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">The<span class="auto-style9"> NSight&copy Personality Questionnaire (NPQ)</span><span class="auto-style8"> is for those who wish to assess the 19 job related personality traits only.&nbsp; These nineteen personality characteristics break down into the following six sub-topics: Decision Making/Problem Solving Skills, Drives, Stress, Interpersonal Communications, Leadership, Commitment/Persistence.&nbsp; This service includes a 9-page analysis detailing the results on </span><span class="auto-style9">NPQ</span><span class="auto-style8">.&nbsp; The investment per individual assessment is $180.&nbsp; However, preferred pricing on quantity purchases can be viewed by clicking </span> <a href="javascript:myopen()"><span class="auto-style8">here</span></a><span class="auto-style8">.</span></p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">The<span class="auto-style9"> NSight&copy Positive Impressions Questionnaire (NPIQ)</span><span class="auto-style8"> is an untimed assessment presenting 50 multiple-choice questions that measure traits to define the type of impression you make on others.&nbsp; Topics involving Self-Perception, Emotional Identification, Synergy, Communication Style and Reliability are highlighted in a 5-6 page analysis of the results.&nbsp; The investment per individual assessment is $79, however quantity pricing that can be viewed by clicking </span> <a href="javascript:myopen()"><span class="auto-style8">here</span></a><span class="auto-style8"> greatly enhances affordability.</span></p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">Dr. Stephen Overcash served as the chief architect of the <span class="auto-style9"> NSight&copy</span><span class="auto-style8">, and as Consulting and Clinical Psychologist for Directional Insight International, Inc.  As a licensed Psychologist, he maintained a full-service private practice in Clinical Psychology along with serving as a consultant in business for over 25 years.  He is a known lecturer, author, and former Adjunct Professor of Psychology for Penn State University. </span> </p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">Penny Reynolds is the founder and president of Texas-based <span class="auto-style9">Directional Insight International, Inc.</span><span class="auto-style8">, publisher of the widely used </span><span class="auto-style9">NSight Aptitude/Personality Assessment</span><span class="auto-style8">.&nbsp; In addition to her expertise in the hiring process, Penny possesses a wealth of personal experience in the sales arena.&nbsp; The evaluation and selection of successful sales personnel is her specialty.&nbsp; For over twenty-five years, she has been actively involved in multiple facets of the assessment industry; including conducting seminars, writing manuals and providing individualized consulting for a variety of businesses.&nbsp; Many corporations benefit from her expertise as she assists them in hiring, promoting, training and retaining a competent work force.&nbsp; Penny participated in the design of the</span><span class="auto-style9"> NSight&copy</span><span class="auto-style8">.</span></p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">Our selection service options are extensive; including the measurement of cognitive resources, personality constructs, customer service know-how, Intelligence Quotient, mechanical abilities, sales &amp; supervisory comprehension, personal interests, attitudes, values and professional integrity.&nbsp; Our development service options include consulting, one-on-one coaching, benchmark studies, retention studies and the design of hiring standards specific to an organization and position. </p>
		<p style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify" class="auto-style8">You may click on <a href="contact_us.aspx" target="_self"><span class="auto-style8">Contact Us</span></a><span class="auto-style8"> to locate Dr. Stephen Overcash and/or Penny Reynolds.</span><br /></p>
		</td>
	</tr>
